  ${
    $d k y F $.  $d y M $.  $d y N $.
    fsumserz.1 $e |- F e. V $.
    $( A finite sum expressed in terms of a partial sum of an infinite
       series.  The recursive definition of follows as ~ fsum1 and ~ fsump1 ,
       which should make our notation clear and from which, along with closure
       ~ fsumclt , we will derive the basic properties of finite sums. $)
    fsumserz $p |- ( N e. ( ZZ> ` M ) -> sum_ k e. ( M ... N ) ( F ` k ) =
                    ( ( <. M , + >. seq F ) ` N ) ) $=
      ( vy cuz cfv wcel cfz co cv csu caddc cop wceq copab cz cres cseqz
      dffsum eluzel2 addex seqzres2 syl fveq1d eqtrd ) DCGHIZCDJKALBHZAMDCNOZFL
